opinions.text:
ORDER
The petition for writ of prohibition, cer-tiorari, or procedendo ad judicium, and petitioner’s motion for stay are denied. The stay previously entered in this case is hereby vacated.

attorneys: John Edward Farley, Chief Legal Counsel, Department for Children and Their Families, Providence, for petitioner.
Barbara Hurst, David L. Martin, Asst. Public Defenders, for respondent.
casebody.head_matter:
In re FRANCIS D.
No. 80-588-M.P.

Jan. 15, 1981.
John Edward Farley, Chief Legal Counsel, Department for Children and Their Families, Providence, for petitioner.
Barbara Hurst, David L. Martin, Asst. Public Defenders, for respondent.
